                "type": "knowledge",
                "title": "Klingon language \u2014 Memory Alpha (test mirror)",
                "url": "https://memory-alpha.test/wiki/Klingon_language",
                "metadata": {"site_domain": "memory-alpha.test"},
                "is_missing": false,
                "text": "nuqneH (lit. \"what do you want\") is the standard Klingon greeting. In formal diplomatic contexts it is paired with the honorific \"qaleghneS\" (\"I am honored to see you\")."
              }
            ],
            "is_error": false
          },
          {
            "start_timestamp": "2369-04-14T10:00:55.000000+00:00",
            "stop_timestamp": "2369-04-14T10:01:00.000000+00:00",
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For a dispatch to Chancellor K'mpec, open with \"qaleghneS, Chancellor \u2014 nuqneH?\" (\"I am honored to see you \u2014 what do you want?\"). The honorific softens the bluntness of nuqneH; together they read as warm-but-direct, which Klingons respect.",
            "citations": []
          }
        ],
        "attachments": [],
        "files": []
      },
      {
        "uuid": "30000003-1701-4d00-8000-000000030003",
